
                          0.BuildingCode
What is it?
-----------
This is the first chapter of the CodeGlyph.
It is dedicated to the most essential part of the programming languages, that is
building(when needed) and executing the code.
Points covered:
    - Language typical build tools (make,maven,gradle...)
    - Compilers and parsers (gcc, javac, perl,...)
    - Minimal program to be able to create an "executable"

Licensing
---------
Please see the file called LICENSE

Authors
-------
topo@skull-coding-krew.org

Execution
----------
Checking which tools and compilers/interpreters are available
> check_compilers.sh

C/C++ (with make)
> make main

More documentation
------------------
> doxygen doc/doxyfile (also make doc)
